Enum XMLHttpRequest.AjaxReadyState

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<XMLHttpRequest.AjaxReadyState>
      • org.safs.net.XMLHttpRequest.AjaxReadyState
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<XMLHttpRequest.AjaxReadyState>
    Enclosing class:
    XMLHttpRequest

    public static enum XMLHttpRequest.AjaxReadyState
extends java.lang.Enum<XMLHttpRequest.AjaxReadyState>
    The enumeration represents Ajax Ready State Code, such as "0", "1", "2", "3" and "4".
    The enumeration has a method value(), which can return the "Ready State code" string format.
    The enumeration has a method text(), which can return the "Ready State text" string format.
